result.execSummary:
The defendant Twaun Ladell Gee was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Tampering with a Global Positioning System Tracking Device, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.465.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in court with attorney Marcella DePeters.  Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in custody.  Kimberly D. Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:  

AS TO COUNT 02:
Court ordered defendant to serve 3 months at the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, straight time, no Huber.  Court would allow good time.

AS TO COUNT 03:
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 months at the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 2, straight time, no Huber.  Court would allow good time.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, if not previously taken and on file.  

Court ordered defendant to pay all the applicable surcharges, costs and disbursements in this action, which would be due 18 months of today's date (on or before 10/07/15).  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Court set restitution at zero at this time, as no victim information has been received, but reserves its right to order restitution within the statutory time period.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in court with attorney Marcella DePeters.  Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in custody.  Kimberly D. Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel advised the court that they have settled this case. Pursuant to negotiations, State moved to dismiss but read in Count 1.  Court granted State's motion and ordered Count 1 dismissed but read in.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as to Count 3, he is now a convicted felon not to possess any firearms and further advised defendant of voting ineligibility. Victim notification needed.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 20.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 7, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defense counsel requested a trial date.  Court set the following briefing schedule:  defense motions due by 3/10/14; State's response due by 3/20/14; defense reply due by 3/25/14.  All motions in limine, jury instructions and witness lists are due prior to the final pretrial date.  Court ordered case adjourned for final pretrial/motion hearing on 3/27/14 at 8:30 a.m. and for jury trial on 4/02/14 at 8:30 a.m.

Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in court with attorney Marcella Depeters.  Defendant Twaun Ladell Gee in custody.  Jay R. Pucek appeared on behalf of Kimberly D. Schoepp for the State of Wisconsin.  Case heard on the morning counsel on request of defense counsel.   Original Information filed by the State.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.
